        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 4:29PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hockley, or 8 miles east of Prairie View, moving northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Prairie View, Hockley, Waller, and Todd Mission.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
